explanation: This solution uses two stacks to achieve O(1) time complexity for each function. The main stack stores the actual elements, and the minStack stores the minimum elements encountered so far. When pushing an element, we check if it's smaller than or equal to the current minimum, and if so, we push it to the minStack. When popping an element, we pop from both stacks. This approach ensures that the minimum element is always at the top of the minStack, allowing for O(1) getMin() time complexity.

